# EC441 – Week 2 Artifact  
## Topic: CRC Error Detection (Link Layer)

## Problem

A sender wants to transmit the following data bits using a CRC error detection scheme.

Data:

1011010110


Generator polynomial:

1101


(a) Determine the number of CRC bits that will be appended to the data.

Answer:


3 bits


(b) Show the augmented data after appending the required number of zeros.

Answer:


1011010110000


(c) Perform the modulo-2 division of the augmented data by the generator polynomial.

Answer:


1011010110000 ÷ 1101


(d) Determine the CRC remainder.

Answer:


110


(e) Write the final transmitted bit sequence.

Answer:


1011010110110


(f) Suppose the receiver obtains the following bit sequence:


1011010110101


Explain whether an error is detected.

Answer:


Remainder = 011
Error detected
